          "defaultParameters": {
            "code": "# Step 3: Range-compressed — full view + adaptive-x crop in ONE block, faithful\n# (surface3d_pair_gl, NO max-pool). The crop is complex-upsampled by F so the\n# range sinc sidelobes are smooth; the crop title/status note the upsample factor.\n# peak_relative=True: pre-azimuth-compression levels still sit well below ADC FS\n# (LNA tuning isn't enough yet); slide the 40 dB dB window so each panel's peak\n# sits at the top of the colormap. Visual jump from n27 → n19 → n18 then shows\n# how much each processing stage raises the signal vs. the noise floor.\nrg_axis = (t_r - t_r_center) * c / 2\n_W = float(view_scale)\n\n_rc = np.where((rg_axis >= -_W) & (rg_axis <= _W))[0]\n_ac = np.where((az_pos  >= -_W) & (az_pos  <= _W))[0]\n_sub = s_rc[_ac[0]:_ac[-1]+1, _rc[0]:_rc[-1]+1]\n_rgx = rg_axis[_rc[0]:_rc[-1]+1]; _azx = az_pos[_ac[0]:_ac[-1]+1]\nF = crop_upsample_factor(len(_azx), len(_rgx))\n_mag = upsample_complex(_sub, F)\n_rgu = upsample_axis(_rgx, F); _azu = upsample_axis(_azx, F)\n\nsurface3d_pair_gl(\n    s_rc, rg_axis, az_pos, 'Step 3: Range-compressed (full view)',\n    _mag, _rgu, _azu, 'Step 3: Range-compressed (x%d crop)' % F,\n    status_b='upsample x%d' % F,\n    peak_relative=True)\n",
            "label": "Plot: Range-compressed",
            "spec": "Display-only: 3-D dB surface of |s_rc| after range compression. Targets are now sharp in range (thin ridges) but still spread in azimuth. Full resolution (no downsampling); the Crop view is complex-upsampled to reveal range sidelobes. Toggle Full/Crop; Expand for a large copy."
